WEBVTT

00:02.635 --> 00:04.296
Hey, Kellogg, how was your weekend?

00:04.371 --> 00:05.963
Complete disaster, Carlton.

00:06.039 --> 00:08.234
I took this girl to see
New Kids on the Block...

00:08.308 --> 00:10.640
and all night she's saying,
"Donnie's so cute.

00:10.710 --> 00:13.076
"Donnie's so sweet, Donnie's so hunky."

00:14.114 --> 00:16.514
What does Donnie have that I don't have?

00:16.816 --> 00:19.341
My guess is you don't have the right stuff.

00:24.190 --> 00:26.988
All right, men, it's History time.

00:28.795 --> 00:30.422
Smith, you're late.

00:30.497 --> 00:33.330
Sorry about that, Coach, but...

00:33.533 --> 00:36.366
I thought I'd run a few laps before class.

00:38.071 --> 00:40.062
Help out the old basketball team.

00:40.140 --> 00:43.109
Good idea, Smith. Good way
to stay ahead of the competition.

00:43.176 --> 00:46.043
Might not be a bad idea
for all you men who are on the team...

00:46.112 --> 00:47.636
to start the day with a few laps.

00:47.714 --> 00:50.444
We run enough laps
at basketball practice, Coach Smiley.

00:50.517 --> 00:53.077
Okay, Hunt, we're not in the gym.

00:53.520 --> 00:57.320
Therefore, you are to refer to me
by my official teaching name:

00:57.457 --> 00:58.822
Professor Smiley.

00:59.426 --> 01:02.486
And for that little slip of the tongue,
20 laps.

01:03.096 --> 01:04.221
All right, men.

01:04.297 --> 01:06.891
Before we start the next chapter
in our History books...

01:06.966 --> 01:09.696
I'm going to give back
the pop quiz from Friday.

01:09.769 --> 01:11.703
I want you all to take these home...

01:11.771 --> 01:14.399
and bring them back
signed by your parents.

01:15.375 --> 01:17.673
I think I aced this one.
How about you, Will?

01:17.744 --> 01:19.473
I think I did just fine.

